sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User
    participant SB as Sandbox<br/>(Z.ai container)
    participant BS as bootstrap.sh
    participant Git as git
    participant SM as Submodules<br/>(standards + guard + skills)
    participant FS as Filesystem<br/>(/home/z/my-project/)
    participant SK as Skill registry<br/>(/home/z/my-project/skills/)

    Note over U,SB: Session start: fresh sandbox,<br/>no custom skills loaded

    U->>SB: bash <(curl bootstrap.sh)
    SB->>BS: invoke bootstrap.sh

    Note over BS: Step 1: ensure Z-ai-platform<br/>is present
    alt Not yet cloned
        BS->>Git: clone --recurse-submodules<br/>github.com/stsgs1980/Z-ai-platform
        Git->>FS: write /home/z/my-project/Z-ai-platform/
    else Already cloned
        BS->>Git: pull --recurse-submodules --ff-only
        Git->>FS: update existing checkout
    end

    Note over BS: Step 2: symlink skills<br/>into sandbox-visible location
    BS->>FS: mkdir -p /home/z/my-project/skills/

    loop for each skill in Z-ai-platform/skills/skills/*/
        BS->>FS: check if symlink exists
        alt Symlink missing
            BS->>FS: ln -s <skill_dir> <sandbox_skills>/<name>
            Note right of FS: LINK <name>
        else Symlink exists
            BS->>FS: refresh symlink (rm + ln -s)
            Note right of FS: updated
        else Real dir conflict
            BS->>FS: mv <name> <name>.sandbox-backup
            BS->>FS: ln -s <skill_dir> <sandbox_skills>/<name>
            Note right of FS: REPLACE<br/>(sandbox version backed up)
        end
    end

    BS->>SB: print summary<br/>(Linked: N, Skipped: M)
    SB-->>U: 35+ custom skills available<br/>via Skill(command="...")

    Note over U: Now Agent can call<br/>any of the toolkit skills:<br/>skill-creator, gepetto,<br/>fullstack-dev, etc.

    U->>SB: Skill(command="skill-creator")
    SB->>SK: lookup symlink
    SK-->>SB: /home/z/my-project/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md
    SB-->>U: skill loaded into context
